fr.apteryx.imageio.dicom
Class StorageCommitmentResultReceiver

Object
  StorageCommitmentResultReceiver

public abstract class StorageCommitmentResultReceiver
extends Object

In order for a Storage Commitment SCU to receive a result from an SCP, a subclass of StorageCommitmentResultReceiver must be defined, implementing the listener method resultReceived. If the Storage Commitment SCU must be able to accept incoming association from the SCP, it must be started using the start method before the request is sent.

resultReceived

public abstract boolean resultReceived(StorageCommitmentSCU.Result result,
                                       DataSet response)
Listener method called when a result is received. This method must be implemented by the user. result contains the information about the SOP instances the SCP commits or does not commit to safekeep. response is a set of data elements that will be sent in the response message. The response is sent if this method returns true. response contains the Tag.status element with a default value of 0 (meaning success) which may be changed in resultReceived. Typical other values for status are 0x110 (processing failure) or 0x213 (resource limitation). Other elements can be added to the data set, like Tag.ErrorComment or Tag.AffectedSOPInstanceUID. See annex C of PS 3.7 in the DICOM standard for possible values for the status codes and additional elements.

If this method returns false, no response is sent, and if another StorageCommitmentResultReceiver instance is listening for Storage Commitment Results, its resultReceived will be called. false should be returned if the transaction id conveyed in the result does not match the transaction id of a request this instance is aware of.

setApplicationTitles

public void setApplicationTitles(String[] calling,
                                 String[] called)
This class will only handle messages from associations using calling and called Application Entitities (AE) titles listed in the specified arrays. Passing a null array means that any AE will be accepted. By default, every called and calling AE are accepted. This method must be called before the service is started.

setApplicationTitles

public void setApplicationTitles(String calling,
                                 String called)
Convenient replacement for setApplicationTitles(String[], String[]) when using single titles. Passing a null String meants that any AE will be accepted.
